rComments: Professor Mo was not there for the students during the strike.  While I understand she had responsibilities to her union, following the end of the strike her stance on the assignments and exam were EXTREMELY unreasonable.  The head of the Dept had given us options to work with, but Mo decided that her word overruled any made by her superiors.

Prof. Mo is one of the most unreasonable professors I've had during the strike. Not only does she demand for her students to finish an exam with no help OR lectures (Since she was part of the union), she is forcing the class to do a "Take home test" instead of cancelling the exam.  With a month of classes missed, she expects same results.  Horrible
